, is smaller than previous estimates in the literature not\naccounting by flavour oscillations inside the disk. The exact value of the\nreduction factor depends on the $\\nu_{e}$ and $\\nu_{x}$ optical depths but it\ncan be as high as $\\sim 5$. The results of this work are a first step toward\nthe analysis of neutrino oscillations in a novel astrophysical context and, as\nsuch, deserve further attention.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Sep 2019 14:34:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 27 Nov 2019 12:38:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 29 Oct 2020 10:38:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 30 Dec 2020 16:34:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-12"}
